oc:kn_06c7f0b6 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SideEffect ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring custom component paths in plugin.json" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Custom paths in plugin.json supplement (do not replace) default directories. Components in both default locations AND custom paths will all load, and name conflicts between them will cause errors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The merge behavior loads from all sources simultaneously, so duplicate names across directories will conflict rather than override." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_0cb12132 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When planning or scaffolding a new plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Start with a minimal plugin (single command, minimal manifest) and expand to standard then advanced patterns as complexity grows. Add custom paths in manifest only when default auto-discovery is insufficient." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Default auto-discovery handles standard layouts; premature optimization of directory structure adds complexity without benefit for simple plugins." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_1c70a9c4 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When naming any plugin component file or directory" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use kebab-case for all directory and file names: commands (e.g., code-review.md), agents (e.g., test-generator.md), skills (e.g., api-testing/), and plugin names in manifest." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Consistent naming ensures reliable auto-discovery and prevents cross-platform issues with spaces or special characters." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_1d7882be a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When validating a plugin before distribution or testing" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before considering a plugin complete, verify: plugin.json is in .claude-plugin/, all component directories are at root level, names use kebab-case, skill directories contain SKILL.md (not README.md), and all paths use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the most common causes of plugins failing to load or components not being discovered." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_878add3b a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any file path within hook commands, MCP server args, script execution, or component files" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never hardcode absolute paths, use relative paths from working directory, or use home directory shortcuts in plugin files. Always use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all intra-plugin references." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Plugins install in different locations depending on user method (marketplace, local, npm), OS conventions, and preferences. Hardcoded paths break portability." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_c3e8b565 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:KnownIssue ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using hierarchical/categorized command structures with subdirectories" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Claude Code does not support nested command discovery automatically. If organizing commands in subdirectories, explicitly list each subdirectory path in the manifest commands array." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Auto-discovery only scans one level deep in the commands/ directory; nested directories require explicit manifest configuration." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_c8d92374 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When organizing plugin directory structure" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All component directories (commands, agents, skills, hooks) MUST be at the plugin root level, NOT nested inside .claude-plugin/. Only the manifest goes inside .claude-plugin/." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Auto-discovery scans specific root-level directories; placing components inside .claude-plugin/ prevents them from being discovered." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_f1356e49 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When structuring plugin documentation and skill content" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Keep SKILL.md lean (~1600 words) focused on core concepts, move detailed information to references/ directory, and provide working examples in examples/ directory. Load deeper layers only as needed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Progressive disclosure manages context window usage efficiently — agents only load what the current task requires." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_f680f11e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating or scaffolding any plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "The plugin.json manifest MUST be located at .claude-plugin/plugin.json — this is the only valid location Claude Code recognizes for plugin discovery." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Claude Code scans specifically for this path during plugin loading; any other location will cause the plugin to be invisible." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

